subSubSection.paragraph:
Other areas have either slight (1% to <25%) pigmentation coverage (caudal fin) or are unpigmented (lower branchial and ventral branchial) (
Table 2
). Internally, the pigmentation coverage of the areas lateral to the elastic ridge is slight and it is absent on the tongue precursor bulb (
Fig. 7a
). Lateral line neuromasts are unpigmented. The caudal fin shape is either spade-like or rounded (
Fig. 2
).

